      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's hard to talk to a hotline when the problem isn't just a sudden mood, but the actual reality of how my life is. i'm not just \"having a bad day,\" i'm living a life that feels like a punishment. when you say it's understandable that i feel this way, it's the first time anyone hasn't just tried to \"fix\" me or tell me to be positive. it just feels like the only way to actually find peace is to not be here anymore. do you think it's wrong to just want the hurting to stop, even if that means everything stops?",
